 Improvisation will be welcomed by anyone striving to comprehend the creative process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aImprovisation (Music). 0aMusicxPhilosophy and aesthetics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  acomedy, dance, theater, music, philosophy, improvisation, art, performing arts, performance, audience, creativity, nonfiction, in the moment, spontaneous, freedom, community, imagination, deleuze, benjamin, kant, adorno, nietzsche, heidegger, aesthetics, thinking, writing, skill, talent, genius, inspiration, cruelty, mimesis, irony, origination.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022666278740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226662800423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226662800/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles